# Lab 1.1 – PowerShell Fundamentals for Identity Automation

## Objective

Learn the foundational concepts of PowerShell and understand how automation supports Identity and Access Management (IAM) operations. The focus of this lab was understanding PowerShell's Verb-Noun command structure, learning how to interpret common cmdlets, and connecting automation to real-world business processes.

---

## Business Scenario

An Identity and Access Management (IAM) team receives recurring requests from Human Resources to provision new employee accounts, assign department access, and generate user reports. Performing these tasks manually is time-consuming and increases the risk of configuration errors.

The objective of this lab was to begin understanding how PowerShell can automate repetitive administrative tasks, improve consistency, and reduce operational effort.

---

## Concepts Learned

### PowerShell Verb-Noun Structure

Understanding how PowerShell commands are organized:

- Get-Service
- Start-Service
- Restart-Service
- Get-Process
- Stop-Process
- Get-ADUser
- New-Item
- Remove-Item
- Test-Connection

This naming convention makes PowerShell easier to learn because command intent is often recognizable without memorizing every cmdlet.

